Josh Meekings has been retrospectively suspended for one game after his handball in the Scottish Cup semi-final . 
  Celtic lost 3-2 to Inverness at Hampden Park on Sunday . 
  Ronny Deila has called for the defender to be spared a Scottish Cup Final ban . 
  FIFA head of referees Jim Boyce says the ban is wrong . 
  Caley Thistle are appealing the suspension . 
 